#### Issue description
When binding `none` to a `unsigned*`, it crashes on function (`foo`) call (v2.01).

#### Reproducible example code
Something similar to:

    m.def("foo", [](unsigned const* const) {
    }, py::arg("level") = py::none())

There seem to be a few instances of the following pattern, eg in `google/datalab/storage/_object.py`:

    try:
      somefunction(someargs)
    except Exception as e:
      raise e

The net effect here is simply truncating the stack trace, which doesn't seem particularly helpful.
